## Critical Implementation Rules

### 🚨 Playwright API - Most Common Mistake
```java
// ❌ NEVER DO THIS - Creates object toString() in URL
String url = baseUrl + "?" + requestOptions;

// ✅ ALWAYS DO THIS - Pass RequestOptions separately
RequestOptions options = RequestOptions.create().setQueryParam("key", value);
APIResponse response = apiRequestContext.get(url, options);
```

### Project Structure
```
src/main/java/
  - Helaper/          # API helper classes
  - constants/        # BaseUrl, EndPoint constants
  - BuildingRequest/  # Request builders
  - pojo/            # Data models
  - com/hunter/utils/ # Utilities

src/test/java/
  - Validation/       # Response validators
  - com/hunter/feature/ # Tests & step definitions
```

### Validation Pattern
When comparing responses by ID:
1. Find matching records by ID
2. Validate ALL fields (not just ID)
3. Use descriptive assertion messages
4. Log validation progress

### Code Standards
- All API calls through Helper classes
- All validations in Validation classes
- Jackson ObjectMapper for JSON
- TestNG assertions with context
- Allure reporting for every API call
- CSV files for test data

### Naming Conventions
- Classes: PascalCase
- Methods: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Packages: lowercase (with exceptions - maintain existing)

## Before Making Changes
1. Read complete files to understand context
2. Check existing patterns and follow them
3. Verify Playwright API usage patterns
4. Ensure all validations are comprehensive
5. Include logging and Allure reporting

## Testing
```bash
mvn test                    # Run tests
mvn allure:serve           # View reports
mvn -Dtest=TestClass test  # Run specific test
```

